<paragraph id="8BE836E2FFE40E08B86391B1FEEF22CF" blockId="68.[264,1321,1417,1603]" box="[264,347,1417,1442]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">
<emphasis id="B923EAF0FFE40E08B86391B1FEEF22CF" box="[264,347,1417,1442]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">Colour</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE836E2FFE40E08B8539189FCA9212E" blockId="68.[264,1321,1417,1603]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">Body black, carinae and clypeus paler, frons lateral with a white mark; legs light to dark brown; forewing hyaline colourless with brown marks along crossveins, veins light brown and in some portions of the wing dark brown, tubercles dark brown, pterostigma dark brown; abdominal sternites dark brown..</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE836E2FFE40E08B8639241FE2D21FF" blockId="68.[264,1325,1657,1883]" box="[264,409,1657,1682]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">
<emphasis id="B923EAF0FFE40E08B8639241FE2D21FF" box="[264,409,1657,1682]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">Morphology</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE836E2FFE40E08B8539299FC8F21D6" blockId="68.[264,1325,1657,1883]" box="[312,827,1697,1723]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">
Body length: 
<specimenCount id="9D51FD6BFFE40E08B8BC929BFE5D21D8" box="[471,489,1699,1717]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
<quantity id="4CAF9B07FFE40E08B89B9299FD3421D6" box="[496,640,1697,1723]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.3" metricValueMax="6.5" metricValueMin="6.1" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" unit="mm" value="6.3" valueMax="6.5" valueMin="6.1">6.1–6.5 mm</quantity>
, 
<specimenCount id="9D51FD6BFFE40E08BBE79299FD1421D8" box="[652,672,1697,1717]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
<quantity id="4CAF9B07FFE40E08BBCD9299FC8321D6" box="[678,823,1697,1723]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.25" metricValueMax="8.1" metricValueMin="6.4" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" unit="mm" value="7.25" valueMax="8.1" valueMin="6.4">6.4–8.1 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE836E2FFE40E08B86392F1FB0A2066" blockId="68.[264,1325,1657,1883]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">Head: Vertex (total length) 1.8 times longer than wide; basal emargination rectangular. Postclypeus with well­developed median carina. Rostrum surpassing hind coxae.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE836E2FFE40E09B8539321FEF1265B" blockId="68.[264,1325,1657,1883]" lastBlockId="69.[264,1323,284,510]" lastPageId="69" lastPageNumber="70" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">Thorax: Hind margin of pronotum obtusely angled. Mesonotum with well­developed carinae. Forewing 3.3–3.6 times longer than wide; costa with 11–25 tubercles; 9 apical cells.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE836E2FFE50E09B853957CFCC02693" blockId="69.[264,1323,284,510]" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">
Male genitalia: Anal tube as in 
<figureCitation id="136C2A67FFE50E09BBDD957CFCF32633" box="[694,839,324,350]" captionStart="FIGURE 42" captionStartId="115.[264,368,1700,1724]" captionTargetBox="[290,1312,352,1651]" captionTargetId="figure-117@115.[273,1329,326,1677]" captionTargetPageId="115" captionText="FIGURE 42. Ozoliarus smithi: A, B anal tube, (A) left lateral, (B) caudal. Ozoliarus dingkana: C, D, E anal tube, (C) caudal, (D) ventral, (E) left lateral; F, G aedeagus, (F) ventral, (G) left lateral; H, I genital styles, (H) ventral, (I) ventrolateral. Ozoliarus quadratistylus: J, K genital styles, (J) ventral, (K) ventrolateral; L, M aedeagus, (L) ventral, (M) left lateral; N, O, P anal tube, (N) ventral, (O) left lateral, (P) caudal. Ozoliarus semicircularis: Q, R, S anal tube, (Q) caudal, (R) ventral, (S) left lateral; T, U aedeagus, (T) ventral, (U) left lateral." pageId="69" pageNumber="70">Figs 42C–E</figureCitation>
; pygophore and genital styles as in 
<figureCitation id="136C2A67FFE50E09BD92957CFEE326EB" captionStart="FIGURE 42" captionStartId="115.[264,368,1700,1724]" captionTargetBox="[290,1312,352,1651]" captionTargetId="figure-117@115.[273,1329,326,1677]" captionTargetPageId="115" captionText="FIGURE 42. Ozoliarus smithi: A, B anal tube, (A) left lateral, (B) caudal. Ozoliarus dingkana: C, D, E anal tube, (C) caudal, (D) ventral, (E) left lateral; F, G aedeagus, (F) ventral, (G) left lateral; H, I genital styles, (H) ventral, (I) ventrolateral. Ozoliarus quadratistylus: J, K genital styles, (J) ventral, (K) ventrolateral; L, M aedeagus, (L) ventral, (M) left lateral; N, O, P anal tube, (N) ventral, (O) left lateral, (P) caudal. Ozoliarus semicircularis: Q, R, S anal tube, (Q) caudal, (R) ventral, (S) left lateral; T, U aedeagus, (T) ventral, (U) left lateral." pageId="69" pageNumber="70">Figs 42H–I</figureCitation>
. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="136C2A67FFE50E09B89A9554FD3D26EB" box="[497,649,364,390]" captionStart="FIGURE 42" captionStartId="115.[264,368,1700,1724]" captionTargetBox="[290,1312,352,1651]" captionTargetId="figure-117@115.[273,1329,326,1677]" captionTargetPageId="115" captionText="FIGURE 42. Ozoliarus smithi: A, B anal tube, (A) left lateral, (B) caudal. Ozoliarus dingkana: C, D, E anal tube, (C) caudal, (D) ventral, (E) left lateral; F, G aedeagus, (F) ventral, (G) left lateral; H, I genital styles, (H) ventral, (I) ventrolateral. Ozoliarus quadratistylus: J, K genital styles, (J) ventral, (K) ventrolateral; L, M aedeagus, (L) ventral, (M) left lateral; N, O, P anal tube, (N) ventral, (O) left lateral, (P) caudal. Ozoliarus semicircularis: Q, R, S anal tube, (Q) caudal, (R) ventral, (S) left lateral; T, U aedeagus, (T) ventral, (U) left lateral." pageId="69" pageNumber="70">Figs 42F–G</figureCitation>
): Phallotheca with a large, bi­ or trifurcated spine (a) ventral; and a ventral ridge with two less distinct humps, one of them bearing pair of short spines (b) fused together, their tips pointing in opposite directions. Flagellum membranous with a slightly sclerotised spine at apex of flagellum.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF28666AFFE50E09B8639333FECD202B" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" startId="69.[264,367,1803,1827]" targetBox="[314,1271,555,1784]" targetPageId="69">
<paragraph id="8BE836E2FFE50E09B8639333FECD202B" blockId="69.[264,1322,1803,1862]" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">
<emphasis id="B923EAF0FFE50E09B8639333FE2C204E" bold="true" box="[264,408,1803,1827]" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">FIGURE 20.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C574D61FFE50E09B8F49334FDC6204E" authorityName="Löcker &amp; Fletcher &amp; Larivière &amp; Gurr" authorityYear="2006" baseAuthorityName="Löcker &amp; Fletcher &amp; Larivière &amp; Gurr" baseAuthorityYear="2006" box="[415,626,1804,1827]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Ozoliarus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dingkana">
<emphasis id="B923EAF0FFE50E09B8F49334FDC6204E" box="[415,626,1804,1827]" italics="true" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">Ozoliarus dingkana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: A habitus; B, C, D head. 
<taxonomicName id="4C574D61FFE50E09BAE59334FB22204E" authorityName="Locker" authorityYear="2006" box="[910,1174,1804,1827]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Ozoliarus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadratistylus">
<emphasis id="B923EAF0FFE50E09BAE59334FB22204E" box="[910,1174,1804,1827]" italics="true" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">Ozoliarus quadratistylus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: E habitus; F, G, H head.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BE836E2FFE60E0AB8639524FEDA2658" blockId="70.[264,1321,284,430]" box="[264,366,284,309]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">
<emphasis id="B923EAF0FFE60E0AB8639524FEDA2658" box="[264,366,284,309]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE836E2FFE60E0AB853957CFE6426C3" blockId="70.[264,1321,284,430]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">
<taxonomicName id="4C574D61FFE60E0AB853957CFE672630" authorityName="Löcker &amp; Fletcher &amp; Larivière &amp; Gurr" authorityYear="2006" baseAuthorityName="Löcker &amp; Fletcher &amp; Larivière &amp; Gurr" baseAuthorityYear="2006" box="[312,467,324,349]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Ozoliarus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dingkana">
<emphasis id="B923EAF0FFE60E0AB853957CFE672630" box="[312,467,324,349]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Oz. dingkana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C574D61FFE60E0ABB07957CFC932630" authorityName="Locker" authorityYear="2006" box="[620,807,324,349]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Ozoliarus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="triangularis">
<emphasis id="B923EAF0FFE60E0ABB07957CFC932630" box="[620,807,324,349]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Oz. triangularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the absence of and spine (A) and a dorsal spine (b). In 
<taxonomicName id="4C574D61FFE60E0AB8F59554FDEE26E8" authorityName="Locker" authorityYear="2006" box="[414,602,364,389]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Ozoliarus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="triangularis">
<emphasis id="B923EAF0FFE60E0AB8F59554FDEE26E8" box="[414,602,364,389]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Oz. triangularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, however, there is an additional set of spines (b) arising from the ventral ridge.
</paragraph>
